import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
In[]:
df = pd.read_csv("../dataset/trans_1.csv")
df2 = pd.read_csv("../dataset/trans_2.csv")

df["date"] = pd.to_datetime(df["date"])
df2["date"] = pd.to_datetime(df2["date"])

df["year"] = df["date"].dt.year
df["month"] = df["date"].dt.month
df["day"] = df["date"].dt.day
df["dow"] = df["date"].dt.day_of_week
df["hour"] = df["date"].dt.hour
df["minute"] = df["date"].dt.minute

df2["year"] = df2["date"].dt.year
df2["month"] = df2["date"].dt.month
df2["day"] = df2["date"].dt.day
df2["dow"] = df2["date"].dt.day_of_week
df2["hour"] = df2["date"].dt.hour
df2["minute"] = df2["date"].dt.minute

columns = ["HUFL", "HULL", "MUFL", "MULL", "LUFL", "LULL", "OT"]
time_columns = ["year", "month", "day", "dow", "hour", "minute"]

Data Visualization

Dataset trans_1.csv

Heatmap

In[]:
sns.heatmap(df.corr(), cmap='coolwarm')
plt.show()

Plot each variable over time

In[]:
for col in columns:
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 8))
    plt.plot(df["date"], df[col])
    plt.title(f"{col} through time")
    plt.ylabel(col)
    plt.show()

Looking for Seasonality/Trends

In[]:
for col in columns:
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(12, 6), squeeze=False)
    for i, time_col in enumerate(time_columns):
        ax = axes[i // 3, i % 3]
        df.groupby(time_col)[col].mean().plot(kind="line", ylim=(-10, 70), title=f"{col} over {time_col}", ylabel=col, ax=ax)
    plt.subplots_adjust(wspace=0.4, hspace=0.5)
    plt.show()

for col in columns:
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 8))
    plt.plot(df2["date"], df2[col])
    plt.title(f"{col} through time")
    plt.ylabel(col)
    plt.show()

Looking for Seasonality/Trends

In[]:
for col in columns:
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(12, 6), squeeze=False)
    for i, time_col in enumerate(time_columns):
        ax = axes[i // 3, i % 3]
        df2.groupby(time_col)[col].mean().plot(kind="line", ylim=(-10, 70), title=f"{col} over {time_col}", ylabel=col, ax=ax)
    plt.subplots_adjust(wspace=0.4, hspace=0.5)
    plt.show()
